body_html:
@gunan

What does the installation command output look like?

I've lost it, because started to train model:
python -m tensorflow.models.image.mnist.convolutional

I don't remember nothing special.
Model was successfully trained

Minibatch loss: 1.595, learning rate: 0.006302
Minibatch error: 0.0%
Validation error: 0.8%
Step 8500 (epoch 9.89), 354.0 ms
Minibatch loss: 1.616, learning rate: 0.006302
Minibatch error: 1.6%
Validation error: 0.9%
Test error: 0.8%

When installing, were you in a terminal that has admin rights?
Without that, the installation may fail because you wont be able to write to system folders.

I wasn't, but python is installed in C:\Users\Ros\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python35 which doesn't require admin rights.
